Educational , interesting, sturdy
I like this product it's very educational, it is interesting and it's very fun to do even for adults, it's sturdy and can be dropped multiple times without any issues, how ever there is one thing I don't like about it and that is that the pen is not attached to it so it is reasonably easy to lose and without it you can't really use it. It is required for you to be with your kid when they use it so they don't misplace the pen. It is totally giftable and cute also little heavier than I expected. Cheers everyone!

Emily
3.0 de 5 estrellas I Wish the Pen Was Attached
Calificado en Estados Unidos el 19 de noviembre de 2023
Compra verificada
My son really likes playing with this, but two criticisms I have are that we lost the pen right away -I wish it was attached! Also, the pen doesn't glide on the letters, it attracts the balls one at a time. So, it doesn't really work for tracing practice. But, my son still finds it entertaining, and you can manipulate the letters with other types of magnets, so that's a plus!
